title: Modified chat formatting for a few special cases
message:
Modified chat formatting for a few special cases

- Timestamps are now a fixed size
- Drink emote, fixes ##17
- Stray colon removed from act emotes

title: Keep notification loader running
message:
Keep notification loader running

If the loader is stopped while the notification drawer is closed and
restarted after it opens, it will show a blank panel for a while. This
makes it look like it's slow to show notifications. It's better to keep
it running and show the notifications instantly.

title: Custom Message (HTML) formatter
message:
Custom Message (HTML) formatter

Implemented a custom Spannalbe formatter/HTML Parser. This way advanced
tags like span with custom classes or styles can be correctly formatted.

For example, NSFW marking and inline spoilers now work correctly and the
whole message formatting can be done using Spans instead of modifing the
TextView attributes.

Fixes #15

title: Added ChatMessageProvider
message:
Added ChatMessageProvider

Save every message into a database. This will make it possible to search
for old notifications, and to the history of the last session. History
is no longer lost if the users disconnects.

Currently, the default message buffer size is 100. It may be a good
idea, to increase that (use a new settings key), or to limit by time. It
might also be interesting to limit the chat view to only the most recent
X messages, instead of everything.

title: Always insert a colon after the nick
message:
Always insert a colon after the nick

When replacing or inserting a nick at the start of the text, a semicolon
and a space character will be added, if they are not there already.

title: Moved Autocomplete to menu
message:
Moved Autocomplete to menu

By registering a context menu on the chat input the default menu
has been disabled. This is confusing for users, because e.g.
paste is no longer easily accesible.
Instead of registering a context menu for autocomplete, it is now
accessible as part of the menu dropdown.

title: Fix back button after disconnect
message:
Fix back button after disconnect

After disconnecting the user needed to press the back button
multiple times to exit the app, because instead of just finising
the app started a new MainActivity.

Adittionally, if the user entered the app by pressing the
notification, the back stack was lost.

Thanks to Toastdeib for reporting this.

title: Don't highlight nicks that are part of html tags.
message:
Don't highlight nicks that are part of html tags.

If the nick is part of a HTML tag, e.g. because it's an emote then
don't highlight the nicks that are between < and >, otherwise we
will generate broken HTML. (Thanks st3rox for reporting this)
